  "prompt": "What is full form of hotel?",
  "response": "The word \"HOTEL\" is not actually an acronym, so it does not have an official \"full form\" in the traditional sense. It comes from the French word \"h\u00f4tel,\" which originally referred to a large townhouse or a place that provides lodging. \n\nOver time, the term evolved to specifically mean a commercial establishment that provides accommodations, meals, and other services to travelers and guests. The modern English word \"hotel\" is derived from this French origin.\n\nSome people have created playful or humorous backronyms like:\n\nH - Hospitality\nO - Overnight\nT - Travelers\nE - Establishment\nL - Lodging\n\nBut these are not the actual origin or official meaning of the word.",
